"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-news-paris-olympics-feisty-mens-sprint-battle-with-jack-carlin-leaves-japans-ota-in-tears\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Japanese sprinter loses 2-1 after being penalised in second sprint  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.6482183486381042, \"rank\": 0.5133643409019799, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 173, \"to\": 275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  Japanese sprinter Ota Kaiya was in tears at theParis Olympicsafter the men's track cyclingindividual sprintcompetition on Thursday, having thought he'd staged a huge upset to defeat Great Britain's Jack Carlin only to be relegated and then defeated in the deciding round.\", \"from\": 277, \"to\": 612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 341, \"end\": 349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.6482183486381042, \"rank\": 0.5133643409019799, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 523, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9984686869377518, \"rank\": 0.0013012523190642908, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 539, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\", \"score\": 0.6064469050884331, \"rank\": 0.6117380191590867, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\"}, {\"begin\": 544, \"end\": 550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999995427698332, \"rank\": 4.5723048886167555e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two sprinters switched lines, banged helmets and clashed elbows during their sprints, with race officials ultimately deciding that Carlin went through the semifinal where he will face defending Olympic champion Harrie Lavreysen (Netherlands).\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999995427698332, \"rank\": 4.5723048886167555e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}, {\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harrie Lavreysen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\"}, {\"begin\": 847, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.886711094329745, \"rank\": 0.1272050675842998, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaiya won the first sprint with a turn of speed and then also beat Carlin in the second sprint.\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"score\": 0.9999998796033723, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaiya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\"}, {\"begin\": 929, \"end\": 935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999995427698332, \"rank\": 4.5723048886167555e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He celebrated after a high-speed body clash but officials overturned the result and awarded the win to Carlin, ruling that Kaiya moved down towards the inside of the track when Carlin was already there.\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1061, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999995427698332, \"rank\": 4.5723048886167555e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}, {\"begin\": 1081, \"end\": 1086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"score\": 0.9999998796033723, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaiya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\"}, {\"begin\": 1135, \"end\": 1141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999995427698332, \"rank\": 4.5723048886167555e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two again went shoulder-to-shoulder during the final 250 metres of the third and deciding sprint.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Carlin appeared to move briefly out of the sprinter's lane but beat Kaiya by 0.014 of a second and was ruled the winner.\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1264, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999995427698332, \"rank\": 4.5723048886167555e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both riders were warned in the final race, Carlin for \\\"irregular movement to prevent the opponent from passing\\\" and Kaiya for dangerous riding, but the officials let the third result stand in favour of Carlin.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1429, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999995427698332, \"rank\": 4.5723048886167555e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}, {\"begin\": 1588, \"end\": 1594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999995427698332, \"rank\": 4.5723048886167555e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team Japan asked for a review but the officials refused to change their result, leaving Kaiya in tears.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999982662757, \"rank\": 1.7277038896006102e-09, \"text\": \"Team Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"score\": 0.9999998796033723, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaiya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought I could get to the medal rounds, but through my own naivety I did not make it, which is really frustrating,\\\" Kaiya said.\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1822, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"score\": 0.9999998796033723, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaiya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1937, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The judges look at the details and decide, so I do not really know, but I think I was relegated for getting too close to my opponent.\\\"\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 2074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Japan sprint coach Jason Niblett admitted that Kaiya had been drawn into a nervous tactical battle by Carlin, leaving him at the mercy of the judges and any punishment for aggressive riding.\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2076, \"end\": 2081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8610691516421288, \"rank\": 0.14736695096992916, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2095, \"end\": 2108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Niblett\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jason Niblett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Niblett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Niblett\"}, {\"begin\": 2123, \"end\": 2128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"score\": 0.9999998796033723, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaiya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\"}, {\"begin\": 2178, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999995427698332, \"rank\": 4.5723048886167555e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sometimes the decision goes our way, sometimes it does not,\\\" the Australian coach admitted.\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2334, \"end\": 2344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.7487594435005782, \"rank\": 0.33364390220829226, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Ideally, I am not in the position to have to fight with judges but the ruling is the ruling.\\\"\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get unlimited access to all of our coverage of the 2024 Olympic Games - including breaking news and analysis reported by our journalists on the ground from every event across road, mountain bike, track and BMX racing as it happens and more.Find out more.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2664, \"end\": 2674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9969864135326849, \"rank\": 0.0030226956220501425, \"text\": \"BMX racing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephen is one of the most experienced members of theCyclingnewsteam, having reported on professional cycling since 1994.\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before becoming Editor-at-large, he was Head of News atCyclingnews.He has previously worked forShift Active Media, ReutersandCycling Weekly.He is a member of the Board of the Association Internationale des Journalistes du Cyclisme (AIJC).\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cyclingnews is part of Future plc, an international media group and leading digital publisher.Visit our corporate site.\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3076, \"end\": 3087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}, {\"begin\": 3099, \"end\": 3109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Future plc\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 Future Publishing Limited Quay House, The Ambury, Bath BA1 1UA.\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3199, \"end\": 3216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0757144714620469e-16, \"text\": \"Future Publishing\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\"}, {\"begin\": 3230, \"end\": 3235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregory_House\", \"score\": 0.9801328888681022, \"rank\": 0.02023